You don&#39;t need to use `bind` if you use [`lang.hitch`][1]. Just pass the param as the third argument. **Any arguments provided after the first two will be passed to the function.**

    onClick: lang.hitch(this, this._createNewLocation, param);

You could use the vanilla `bind()` method instead if you prefer:

    onClick: _createNewLocation.bind(this, param);

    myObject.prototype._createNewLocation = function(param, evt) {
        console.log(param, evt);
    }


  [1]: https://dojotoolkit.org/reference-guide/1.9/dojo/_base/lang.html#dojo-base-lang-hitch

